<div class="problem"><p>
In the discussion following <a class="knowl" acro="OBNM" type="Theorem" title="Orthonormal Bases and Normal Matrices" knowl="./knowls/theorem.OBNM.knowl">Theorem OBNM</a> we comment that the equation $\hat{\vect{x}} = \adjoint{U}\vect{x}$ is just <a class="knowl" acro="COB" type="Theorem" title="Coordinates and Orthonormal Bases" knowl="./knowls/theorem.COB.knowl">Theorem COB</a> in disguise.  Formulate this observation more formally and prove the equivalence.
</p></div>
